> 
> FYI, here's some info that was posted to this list by David Preston (who
> in turn obtained this info from VDO) about 3 years ago.  If you think your
> sender is good and your gauge is inaccurate, you can check it like this:
> 
> **********************************
> How To Check 300 degree Oil Temp Sender
> Disconnect wire from sender.
> Check the resistance between the terminal and ground
> 
> 322 Ohms =  120  Degrees
> 105 Ohms =  180  Degrees
> 64 Ohms =   210   Degrees
> 35 Ohms =  250    Degrees
> 18 Ohms =  300    Degrees
> **********************************
> 
> Mike g.
